 The letter dated May 7 , 1912 , was sent from White Star Lines to Christopher Moody , the brother of 24-year-old officer James Moody , died after the Titanic hit an iceberg on its maiden voyage .
In it , company bosses demand £ 20 - the equivalent of £ 2,000 in today 's money - to return his body to England .
The letter asks for £ 20 , almost £ 20,000 money to have Mr Moody 's remains sent to his home in Scarborough .